    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>Your companion is a particularly large bat, such as a giant bat.</p>\n<p><strong>Size</strong> Small</p>\n<p><strong>Melee</strong> <span class=\"pf2-icon\">1</span> jaws (finesse), <strong>Damage</strong> 1d6 piercing</p>\n<p><strong>Melee</strong> <span class=\"pf2-icon\">1</span> wing (agile, finesse), <strong>Damage</strong> 1d4 slashing</p>\n<p><strong>Str</strong> +2, <strong>Dex</strong> +3, <strong>Con</strong> +2, <strong>Int</strong> -4, <strong>Wis</strong> +1, <strong>Cha</strong> +0</p>\n<p><strong>Hit Points</strong> 6</p>\n<p><strong>Skill</strong> Stealth</p>\n<p><strong>Senses</strong> echolocation 20 feet (the bat can use hearing as a precise sense within this range), low-light vision</p>\n<p><strong>Speed</strong> 15 feet, fly 30 feet</p>\n<p><strong>Support Benefit</strong> Your bat flaps around your foes' arms and faces, getting in the way of their attacks. Until the start of your next turn, creatures in your bat's reach that you damage with Strikes take a -1 circumstance penalty to their attack rolls.</p>\n<p><strong>Advanced Maneuver</strong> @Compendium[pf2e-animal-companions.AC-Advanced-Maneuvers.ODGf6brAHHKrSAPo]{Wing Thrash}</p>"
